tldr: The user requested a review of the sleep questionnaire implementation
  against acceptance criteria and the addition of missing features. The agent
  successfully implemented a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with safety messaging
  and detection for Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) in both the web
  and PDF reports.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification and Statement of Work. The
  agent performed an in-depth analysis, identifying several gaps and missing
  features. Following this review, the agent began implementing the prioritized
  action items. Key implementations included adding a 1-10 severity scale for
  tiredness interference, complete with critical safety warnings for high
  scores, and integrating detection and specific recommendations for Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA). These changes were applied across the
  application, including data types, validation schemas, UI components, and both
  web and PDF report generation, enhancing the questionnaire's diagnostic
  capabilities and user guidance.
